ry after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Hereward was born about 1214, in Devon, England, United Kingdom as the son of John Hereward and Ellen Floyer. He married Dulcia Stapleton before 1240, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 5 daughters. He died after 1324, in his hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1214–after 1324":"umbes 1214–pärast 1324","1214–1324":"1214–1324","–Female":"Surnud","1214–1320":"1214–1320","1244–Female":"1244–Surnud","–1245":"–1245","–1327":"–1327","–Male":"Surnud","1268–Female":"1268–Surnud","1307-1327":"1307 kuni 1327","Abt 1214":"umbes 1214","after 1324":"pärast 1324","1327":"1327","Bef 1240":"enne 1240","1324":"1324","1214":"1214","1268":"1268","1245":"1245","1244":"1244","1320":"1320","after 1320":"pärast 1320","after 1245":"pärast 1245","Doddescot, Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Doddescot (Dodscott), Devonshire,England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hinton Saint George, Crewkerne, Somerset, England":"Hinton St George, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pinhoe, Devonshire,England":"Pinhoe, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hinton, St grg, England":"Hinton, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1214–after 1324":"noin 1214–1324 jälkeen","1214–1324":"1214–1324","–Female":"Kuollut","1214–1320":"1214–1320","1244–Female":"1244–Kuollut","–1245":"–1245","–1327":"–1327","–Male":"Kuollut","1268–Female":"1268–Kuollut","1307-1327":"vuodesta 1307 vuoteen 1327","Abt 1214":"noin 1214","after 1324":"1324 jälkeen","1327":"1327","Bef 1240":"ennen vuotta 1240","1324":"1324","1214":"1214","1268":"1268","1245":"1245","1244":"1244","1320":"1320","after 1320":"1320 jälkeen","after 1245":"1245 jälkeen","Dodd